n","url":"https://torrentfreak.com/uploading-pirated-books-via-bittorrent-qualifies-as-fair-use-meta/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285960","date_published":"2026-03-07T09:18:40Z","author":{"name":"askl","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=askl"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285876","title":"Show HN: µJS, a 5KB alternative to Htmx and Turbo with zero dependencies","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eI built µJS because I wanted AJAX navigation without the verbosity of HTMX or the overhead of Turbo.\u003cp\u003eIt intercepts links and form submissions, fetches pages via AJAX, and swaps fragments of the DOM. Single \u003cscript\u003e tag, one call to `mu.init()`. No build step, no dependencies.\u003cp\u003eKey features: patch mode (update multiple fragments in one request), SSE support, DOM morphing via idiomorph, View Transitions, prefetch on hover, polling, and full HTTP verb support on any element.\u003cp\u003eAt ~5KB gzipped, it's smaller than HTMX (16KB) and Turbo (25KB), and works with any backend: PHP, Python, Go, Ruby, whatever.\u003cp\u003ePlayground: \u003ca href=\"https://mujs.org/playground\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://mujs.org/playground\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eComparison with HTMX and Turbo: \u003ca href=\"https://mujs.org/comparison\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://mujs.org/comparison\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eAbout the project creation, why and when: \u003ca href=\"https://mujs.org/about\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://mujs.org/about\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eGitHub: \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/Digicreon/muJS\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://github.com/Digicreon/muJS\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eHappy to discuss the project.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285876\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285876\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 102\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 39\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://mujs.org","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285876","date_published":"2026-03-07T08:59:11Z","author":{"name":"amaury_bouchard","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=amaury_bouchard"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285846","title":"QGIS 4.0","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://changelog.qgis.org/en/version/4.0/\"\u003ehttps://changelog.qgis.org/en/version/4.0/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285846\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285846\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 192\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 46\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://changelog.qgis.org/en/version/4.0/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285846","date_published":"2026-03-07T08:53:47Z","author":{"name":"jonbaer","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=jonbaer"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285422","title":"Sarvam 105B, the first competitive Indian open source LLM","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://www.sarvam.ai/blogs/sarvam-30b-105b\"\u003ehttps://www.sarvam.ai/blogs/sarvam-30b-105b\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285422\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285422\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 169\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 60\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://www.sarvam.ai/blogs/sarvam-30b-105b","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47285422","date_published":"2026-03-07T07:43:57Z","author":{"name":"logicchains","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=logicchains"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47283665","title":"UUID package coming to Go standard library","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/62026\"\u003ehtt